d Cup five-wicket hauls|access-date=5 July 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180122203018/http://stats.espncricinfo.com/ci/engine/records/bowling/most_5wi_career.html?id=12;type=trophy|archive-date=22 January 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n|Most four-wicket hauls (and over)\n|{{flagicon|Australia}} [[Mitchell Starc]]\n|6\n|{{flagicon|SA}} [[Imran Tahir]]\n|5\n|<ref>{{cite web|url=http://stats.espncricinfo.com/ci/engine/records/bowling/most_4wi_career.html?id=12;type=trophy|title=World Cup four-wicket hauls (and over)|access-date=7 July 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180121192052/http://stats.espncricinfo.com/ci/engine/records/bowling/most_4wi_career.html?id=12;type=trophy|archive-date=21 January 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n|-\n| rowspan=\"11\" |Most wickets in consecutive balls\n| rowspan=\"11\" | {{flagicon|Sri Lanka}} [[Lasith Malinga]]\n| rowspan=\"11\" |4 v [[South Africa cricket team|South Africa]] ([[2007 Cricket World Cup|2007]])\n|-\n|{{flagicon|India}} [[Chetan Sharma]] ||3 v [[New Zealand Cricket Team|New Zealand]] ([[1987 Cricket World Cup|1987]])\n| rowspan=\"10\" |<ref name=\"World Cup hat-tricks\">{{cite web | url = http://uk.reuters.com/article/2015/03/18/uk-cricket-world-hattricks-idUKKBN0ME0L920150318 | title = World Cup hat-tricks | date = 18 March 2015 | accessdate = 19 March 2015 | publisher = Reuters | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20150402125046/http://uk.reuters.com/article/2015/03/18/uk-cricket-world-hattricks-idUKKBN0ME0L920150318 | archive-date = 2 April 2015 | url-status = live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.cricinfo.com/wc2007/content/story/287713.html | title = Full length, full reward | date = 28 March 2007 | accessdate = 24 October 2009 | publisher = Cricinfo | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20090712163401/http://www.cricinfo.com/wc2007/content/story/287713.html | archive-date = 12 July 2009 | url-status = live }}</ref>\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Pakistan}} [[Saqlain Mushtaq]] ||3 v [[Zimbabwe Cricket Team|Zimbabwe]] ([[1999 Cricket World Cup|1999]])\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Sri Lanka}} [[Chaminda Vaas]] ||3 v [[Bangladesh national cricket team|Bangladesh]] ([[2003 Cricket World Cup|2003]])\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Australia}} [[Brett Lee]] ||3 v [[Kenya national cricket team|Kenya]] ([[2003 Cricket World Cup|2003]])\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Sri Lanka}} [[Lasith Malinga]] ||3 v [[Kenya national cricket team|Kenya]] ([[2011 Cricket World Cup|2011]])\n|-\n|{{flagicon|West Indies}} [[Kemar Roach]] ||3 v [[Netherlands national cricket team|Netherlands]] ([[2011 Cricket World Cup|2011]]) \n|-\n|{{flagicon|England}} [[Steven Finn (cricketer)|Steven Finn]] ||3 v [[Australia national cricket team|Australia]] ([[2015 Cricket World Cup|2015]]) \n|-\n|{{flagicon|South Africa}} [[JP Duminy]] ||3 v [[Sri Lanka national cricket team|Sri Lanka]] ([[2015 Cricket World Cup|2015]])\n|-\n|{{flagicon|India}} [[Mohammad Shami]] ||3 v [[Afghanistan Cricket Board|Afghanistan]] ([[2019 Cricket World Cup|2019]])\n|-\n|{{cricon|NZL}} [[Trent Boult]] ||3 v [[Australia cricket team|Australia]] ([[2019 Cricket World Cup|2019]])\n|-\n|[[Fast bowling|Fastest bowler]]\n|{{flagicon|Pakistan}} [[Shoaib Akhtar]] || 161.3{{nbsp}}km/h (100.23{{nbsp}}mph) v England ([[2003 Cricket World Cup|2003]])\n|\n|\n|<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.guinnessworldrecords.com/records-10000/fastest-bowl-of-a-cricket-ball/|title=Fastest delivery of a cricket ball (male)|work=[[Guinness World Records]]|accessdate=17 June 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140915020152/http://www.guinnessworldrecords.com/records-10000/fastest-bowl-of-a-cricket-ball/|archive-date=15 September 2014|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|}\n\n[[Glenn McGrath]] dominates the bowling records, and holds all but three of the records. [[Lasith Malinga]] became the first player to take four wickets in four balls at an international level in the 2007 World Cup, against South Africa.<ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.cricinfo.com/wc2007/content/story/287688.html|title = Malinga's hat-trick and South Africa's edge|publisher = Cricinfo|accessdate = 2 November 2009|first = Dileep|last = Premachandran|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20100417080125/http://www.cricinfo.com/wc2007/content/story/287688.html|archive-date = 17 April 2010|url-status = live}}</ref> [[Chaminda Vaas]] took four wickets in five balls against Bangladesh in 2003, including wickets with the first three balls of the match. There have also been hat tricks in Cricket World Cups by [[Chetan Sharma]], [[Saqlain Mushtaq]], [[Brett Lee]], [[Kemar Roach]], [[Steven Finn (cricketer)|Steven Finn]] , [[JP Duminy]] and [[Mohammed Shami]].<ref name=\"World Cup hat-tricks\"/><ref>{{cite web | url = http://static.cricinfo.com/db/STATS/WC/BOWLING/WC_BOWL_HAT-TRICKS.html | title = World Cups \u2013 Hat Tricks | accessdate = 2 November 2009 | publisher = Cricinfo | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20101230160721/http://static.cricinfo.com/db/STATS/WC/BOWLING/WC_BOWL_HAT-TRICKS.html | archive-date = 30 December 2010 | url-status = live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.cricinfo.com/ci/engine/match/65243.html | title = ICC World Cup \u2013 10th match, Pool B | publisher = Cricinfo | accessdate = 2 November 2009 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20091124165028/http://www.cricinfo.com/ci/engine/match/65243.html | archive-date = 24 November 2009 | url-status = live }}</ref>\n\n[[Chetan Sharma]] was the first bowler to take a hat-trick in a Cricket World Cup. [[Lasith Malinga]] was the first bowler to take 2 hat-tricks in Cricket World Cup matches.\n\n===One tournament===\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Record\n! colspan=\"3\" | First\n! colspan=\"3\" | Second\n! Ref(s)\n|-\n|Most wickets in a tournament\n|{{flagicon|Australia}} [[Mitchell Starc]]\n| 27 (10 matches)\n| [[2019 Cricket World Cup|2019]]\n|  {{flagicon|Australia}} [[Glenn McGrath]]\n| 26 (11 matches)\n| [[2007 Cricket World Cup|2007]]\n|<ref>{{cite web|url=http://stats.espncricinfo.com/ci/engine/records/bowling/most_wickets_series.html?id=12;type=trophy|title=World cup most wickets in a tournament|publisher=ESPNCricinfo|access-date=23 March 2011|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101209061807/http://stats.espncricinfo.com/ci/engine/records/bowling/most_wickets_series.html?id=12;type=trophy|archive-date=9 December 2010|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==Fielding==\nWhile records for best fielders have varied through different World Cups, the records for wicketkeepers have been occupied by [[Kumar Sangakkara]] who holds the record for most dismissals overall and [[Adam Gilchrist]] which holds the record for most dismissals by a wicketkeeper in one tournament and in one match.\n[[File:Sangakkara (portrait).jpg|thumb|Highest dismissals as a wicket-keeper:Kumar Sangakkara]]\n\n===Overall===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!| Record\n! colspan=\"2\" | First\n! colspan=\"2\" | Second\n!| Ref(s)\n|-\n|Most dismissals ([[wicketkeeper]])\n|{{flagicon|Sri Lanka}} [[Kumar Sangakkara]]\n|54\n|{{flagicon|Australia}} [[Adam Gilchrist]]\n|52\n|<ref>{{cite web | url = http://stats.cricinfo.com/ci/engine/records/keeping/most_dismissals_career.html?id=12;type=trophy | publisher = Cricinfo | accessdate = 25 October 2009 | title = Records \u2013 World Cup \u2013 Most dismissals | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20090318011948/http://stats.cricinfo.com/ci/engine/records/keeping/most_dismissals_career.html?id=12;type=trophy | archive-date = 18 March 2009 | url-status = live }}</ref>\n|-\n|Most catches ([[Fielding (cricket)|fielder]])\n|{{flagicon|Australia}} [[Ricky Ponting]]\n|28\n|{{flagicon|England}} [[Joe Root]]\n|20\n|<ref>{{cite web | url = http://stats.cricinfo.com/ci/engine/records/fielding/most_catches_career.html?id=12;type=trophy | title = Records \u2013 World Cup \u2013 Most catches | accessdate = 25 October 2009 | publisher = Cricinfo | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20090318011549/http://stats.cricinfo.com/ci/engine/records/fielding/most_catches_career.html?id=12;type=trophy | archive-date = 18 March 2009 | url-status = live }}</ref>\n|}\n\n===One tournament===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!| Record\n! colspan=\"3\" | First\n! colspan=\"3\" | Second\n!| Ref(s)\n|-\n|Most dismissals ([[wicketkeeper]])\n|{{flagicon|Australia}} [[Adam Gilchrist]]\n|21\n|[[2003 Cricket World Cup|2003]]\n|{{flagicon|New Zealand}} [[Tom Latham (cricketer)|Tom Latham]]\n|21\n|[[2019 Cricket World Cup|2019]]\n|<ref>{{cite web | url = http://stats.cricinfo.com/ci/engine/records/keeping/most_dismissals_series.html?id=12;type=trophy | publisher = Cricinfo | accessdate = 25 October 2009 | title = Cricket Records \u2013 Records \u2013 World Cup \u2013 Most dismissals in a series | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20090318011958/http://stats.cricinfo.com/ci/engine/records/keeping/most_dismissals_series.html?id=12;type=trophy | archive-date = 18 March 2009 | url-status = live }}</ref>\n|-\n|Most catches ([[Fielding (cricket)|fielder]])\n|{{flagicon|England}} [[Joe Root]]\n|13\n|[[2019 Cricket World Cup|2019]]\n|{{flagicon|Australia}} [[Ricky Ponting]]\n|11\n|[[2003 Cricket World Cup|2003]]\n|<ref>{{cite web | url = http://stats.cricinfo.com/ci/engine/records/fielding/most_catches_series.html?id=12;type=trophy | title = Records \u2013 Records \u2013 World Cup \u2013 Most catches in a series | publisher = Cricinfo | accessdate = 25 October 2009 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20090318011557/http://stats.cricinfo.com/ci/engine/records/fielding/most_catches_series.html?id=12;type=trophy | archive-date = 18 March 2009 | url-status = live }}</ref>\n|}\n\n===One match===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!| Record\n! colspan=\"3\" | First\n!| Ref(s)\n|-\n|Most dismissals ([[wicketkeeper]])\n|{{flagicon|Australia}} [[Adam Gilchrist]]<br>{{flagicon|Pakistan}} [[Sarfraz Ahmed]]\n|6\n|[[2003 Cricket World Cup|2003]]<br>[[2015 Cricket World Cup|2015]]\n|<ref>{{cite web | url = http://stats.cricinfo.com/ci/engine/records/keeping/most_dismissals_innings.html?id=12;type=trophy | accessdate = 25 October 2009 | publisher = Cricinfo | title = Records \u2013 World Cup \u2013 Most dismissals in an innings | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20090318011953/http://stats.cricinfo.com/ci/engine/records/keeping/most_dismissals_innings.html?id=12;type=trophy | archive-date = 18 March 2009 | url-status = live }}</ref>\n|-\n|Most catches ([[Fielding (cricket)|fielder]])\n|{{flagicon|India}} [[Mohammed Kaif]]<br>{{flagicon|Bangladesh}} [[Soumya Sarkar]]<br>{{flagicon|Pakistan}} [[Umar Akmal]]<br>{{flagicon|England}} [[Chris Woakes]] \n|4\n|[[2003 Cricket World Cup|2003]]<br>[[2015 Cricket World Cup|2015]]<br>[[2015 Cricket World Cup|2015]]<br>[[2019 Cricket World Cup|2019]]\n|<ref>{{cite web | url = http://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Records/World_Cup/Overall/Fielding/Most_Catches_by_Fielder_in_an_Innings.html | accessdate = 20 June 2019 | publisher = Cricket Archive | title = World Cup Most Catches in an Innings | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20190620134943/http://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Records/World_Cup/Overall/Fielding/Most_Catches_by_Fielder_in_an_Innings.html | archive-date = 20 June 2019 | url-status = live }}</ref><!--Note : Cricinfo shows Jonny Bairstow on their version of this list, but he made 4 catches as a stand-in wicketkeeper in 2019 WC -->\n|}\n\n===Extras===\nAn [[Extra (cricket)|extra]] is a [[run (cricket)|run]] scored by a means other than a [[batsman]] hitting the [[cricket ball|ball]]. Other than runs scored off the bat from a [[no-ball]], a batsman is not given credit for extras and the extras are tallied separately on the scorecard and count only towards the team's score.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!| Record\n! colspan=\"2\" | First\n! colspan=\"2\" | Second\n!| Ref(s)\n|-\n|Most [[extra (cricket)|extras]] conceded in one innings\n|{{cr|Scotland}} v {{cr|Pakistan}} ([[1999 Cricket World Cup|1999]])\n|59 (5 [[Bye (cricket)|b]], 6&nbsp;[[Leg bye|lb]], 33 [[Wide (cricket)|w]], 15 [[No-ball|nb]])\n|{{cr|India}} v {{cr|Zimbabwe}} ([[1999 Cricket World Cup|1999]])\n|51 (0 b, 14&nbsp;lb, 21 w, 16 nb) \n|<ref>{{cite web | url = http://content-usa.cricinfo.com/records/engine/records/team/most_extras_innings.html?id=12;type=trophy |publisher = Cricinfo| accessdate = 25 October 2009| title = World Cup \u2013 Records \u2013 Most extras in an innings}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==Other Records==\n\nThere are certain records other than batting, bowling or fielding. These records include participation records, hosting records etc.\n\n===Grounds===\nThe World Cup has been held in England five times. As a result, English grounds have hosted the most World Cup matches.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" \n|-\n!| Record\n! colspan=\"2\" | First\n! colspan=\"2\" | Second\n! Ref(s)\n|-\n|Most matches hosted by a ground\n|{{flagicon|England}} [[Old Trafford (cricket ground)|Old Trafford]], [[Manchester]]\n| 17\n|{{flagicon|England}} [[Headingley Cricket Ground|Headingley]], [[Leeds]]<br/>\n{{flagicon|England}} [[Edgbaston Cricket Ground|Edgbaston]], [[Birmingham]]\n| 16\n|<ref>{{cite web | url = http://stats.espncricinfo.com/ci/engine/stats/index.html?class=2;filter=advanced;groupby=ground;orderby=matches;template=results;trophy=12;type=team | title = Matches per ground | publisher = Cricinfo | accessdate = 20 June 2019 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20150911194457/http://stats.espncricinfo.com/ci/engine/stats/index.html?class=2;filter=advanced;groupby=ground;orderby=matches;template=results;trophy=12;type=team | archive-date = 11 September 2015 | url-status = live }}</ref>\n|}\n\n===Umpires===\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" \n|-\n!| Record\n! colspan=\"2\" | First\n! colspan=\"2\" | Second\n!| Ref(s)\n|-\n|Most matches as umpire in World Cup \n|{{flagicon|England}} [[David Shepherd (umpire)|David Shepherd]]\n| 46\n|{{flagicon|West Indies}} [[Steve Bucknor]]\n| 45\n|<ref name=ump>{{cite web|url=http://content-usa.cricinfo.com/records/engine/records/individual/most_matches_umpire.html?id=12;type=trophy|title=Cricket Records \u2013 Records \u2013 World Cup \u2013 Most matches as umpire |publisher=Cricinfo|accessdate=25 October 2009}}</ref>\n|-\n|Most finals as umpire in World Cup \n|{{flagicon|West Indies}} [[Steve Bucknor]]\n| 5\n|{{flagicon|England}} [[David Shepherd (umpire)|David Shepherd]] <br>{{flagicon|England}} [[Dickie Bird]]\n| 3\n|<ref name=umpfinals>{{cite web|url=http://stats.espncricinfo.com/ci/engine/stats/index.html?class=2;filter=advanced;final_type=1;orderby=matches_umpire;template=results;trophy=12;type=official|title=Cricket World Cup Records \u2013 Most finals as umpire |publisher=Cricinfo|accessdate=21 April 2015}}</ref>\n|}\n\n===Appearances===\n\n====Tournaments====\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Appearances\n!Player\n!Span\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |6\n|{{flagicon|Pakistan}} [[Javed Miandad]]\n|1975-1996\n|-\n|{{flagicon|India}} [[Sachin Tendulkar]]\n|1992-2011\n|-\n| rowspan=\"10\" |5\n|{{flagicon|PAK}} [[Shahid Afridi]]\n|1999-2015\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Pakistan}} [[Imran Khan]]\n|1975-1992\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Pakistan}} [[Wasim Akram]]\n|1987-2003\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Pakistan}} [[Inzamam-ul-haq]]\n|1992-2007\n|-\n|{{flagicon|SA}} [[Jacques Kallis]]\n|1996-2011\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Australia}} [[Ricky Ponting]]\n|1996-2011\n|-\n|{{flagicon|West Indies}} [[Chris Gayle]]\n|2003-2019\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Sri Lanka}} [[Arjuna Ranatunga|Arjuna Ranathunga]]\n|1983-1999\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Sri Lanka}} [[Sanath Jayasuriya]]\n|1992-2007\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Sri Lanka}} [[Mahela Jayawardene]]\n|1999-2015\n|}\n\n====Matches====\nThe top 10 list is dominated by players who have appeared in five World Cup tournaments.\n \n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!| Record\n! colspan=\"2\" | First\n! colspan=\"2\" | Second\n!| Ref(s)\n|-\n|Most appearances in World Cup \n|{{flagicon|Australia}} [[Ricky Ponting]]\n| 46\n|{{flagicon|India}} [[Sachin Tendulkar]]\n| 45\n|<ref>{{cite web | url = http://stats.cricinfo.com/ci/engine/records/individual/most_matches_career.html?id=12;type=trophy | title = Records / World Cup / Most matches | publisher = Cricinfo | accessdate = 26 March 2015 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20090318011938/http://stats.cricinfo.com/ci/engine/records/individual/most_matches_career.html?id=12;type=trophy | archive-date = 18 March 2009 | url-status = live }}</ref>\n|}\n\n====Representing more than one country====\n\n[[Anderson Cummins]], [[Kepler Wessels]], [[Ed Joyce]] and [[Eoin Morgan]] are the only four players to have represented two different countries in [[Cricket World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web| url = http://m.sportzwiki.com/cricket/players-to-have-played-world-cups-for-two-different-countries| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20150207173042/http://m.sportzwiki.com/cricket/players-to-have-played-world-cups-for-two-different-countries| url-status = dead| archive-date = 7 February 2015| title = Players to Have Played World Cups for two different Countries| accessdate = 17 December 2014}}</ref>\n\n===Most World Cup Titles===\n[[Adam Gilchrist]], [[Glenn McGrath]] and [[Ricky Ponting]] share the record of three World Cup titles. Each was a member of Australia's winning teams of 1999, 2003 and 2007.\n\n===Age===\nA total of 40 players aged 19 years old or under have made an appearance in the World Cup<ref>{{cite web | url = http://stats.espncricinfo.com/ci/engine/stats/index.html?agemax2=19;agemin2=15;ageval2=age;class=2;filter=advanced;orderby=matches;size=100;template=results;trophy=12;type=allround |title=World Cup players aged 19 or less |publisher=Cricinfo |accessdate=3 June 2019}}</ref> and 19 players aged more than 40 have played in the competition.<ref>{{cite web| url = http://stats.espncricinfo.com/ci/engine/stats/index.html?agemin1=40;ageval1=age;class=2;filter=advanced;orderby=matches;template=results;trophy=12;type=allround| title = World Cup players aged 40 or more| publisher = Cricinfo| accessdate = 3 June 2019| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20161124103139/http://stats.espncricinfo.com/ci/engine/stats/index.html?agemin1=40;ageval1=age;class=2;filter=advanced;orderby=matches;template=results;trophy=12;type=allround| archive-date = 24 November 2016| url-status = live}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!| Record\n! colspan=\"3\" | First\n! colspan=\"3\" | Second\n!| Ref(s)\n|-\n|Youngest player\n|{{flagicon|Canada}} [[Nitish Kumar (cricketer)|Nitish Kumar]]\n|16 years, 283 days\n|[[2011 Cricket World Cup|2011]]\n|{{flagicon|Bangladesh}} [[Talha Jubair]]\n|17 years, 70 days\n|[[2003 Cricket World Cup|2003]]\n|<ref name=young>{{cite web | url = https://www.tentaran.com/hattrick-in-cricket-world-cup/ | title = Hattrick in Cricket World Cup {{!}} ICC Cricket World Cup records | publisher = Tentaran.com | accessdate = 11 June 2019}}</ref><ref name=younger>{{cite web | url = https://www.tentaran.com/hattrick-in-cricket-world-cup/ | title = Hattrick in Cricket World Cup {{!}} ICC Cricket World Cup records | publisher = Tentaran.com | accessdate = 11 June 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n|Oldest player\n|{{flagicon|Netherlands}} [[Nolan Clarke]]\n|47 years, 257 days\n|[[1996 Cricket World Cup|1996]]\n|{{flagicon|Zimbabwe}} [[John Traicos]]\n|44 years, 306 days\n|[[1992 Cricket World Cup|1992]]\n|<ref>{{cite web | url = https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Records/World_Cup/Overall/Miscellaneous/Oldest_Players.html | title = World Cup Oldest Players | publisher = Cricket Archive | accessdate = 25 March 2015 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20150402100235/http://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Records/World_Cup/Overall/Miscellaneous/Oldest_Players.html | archive-date = 2 April 2015 | url-status = live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url = http://static.cricinfo.com/db/STATS/WC/INDIVIDUAL/WC_OLDEST_PLAYERS.html | title = World Cup \u2013 Oldest Players (up to 2007) | publisher = Cricinfo | accessdate = 25 October 2009 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20120304051447/http://static.cricinfo.com/db/STATS/WC/INDIVIDUAL/WC_OLDEST_PLAYERS.html | archive-date = 4 March 2012 | url-status = live }}</ref>\n|}\n\n===Captaincy===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!| Record\n! colspan=\"2\" | First\n! colspan=\"2\" | Second\n!| Ref(s)\n|-\n|Most matches as captain<ref name='WCcaptain'>{{cite web|url=http://content-usa.cricinfo.com/records/engine/records/individual/most_matches_as_captain.html?id=12;type=trophy|title=Most matches as captain \u2013 World Cup|publisher=Cricinfo|accessdate=11 June 2007}}</ref>\n|{{flagicon|Australia}} [[Ricky Ponting]]\n|29\n|{{flagicon|New Zealand}} [[Stephen Fleming]]\n|27\n|<ref name=capt>{{cite web | url = http://stats.cricinfo.com/ci/engine/records/individual/most_matches_as_captain.html?id=12;type=trophy | title = Cricket Records \u2013 Records \u2013 World Cup \u2013 Most matches as captain | publisher = Cricinfo | accessdate = 25 October 2009 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20090318011936/http://stats.cricinfo.com/ci/engine/records/individual/most_matches_as_captain.html?id=12;type=trophy | archive-date = 18 March 2009 | url-status = live }}</ref>\n|-\n|Best win % as captain (min. 10 matches)<ref name='WCcaptain'/>\n|{{flagicon|Australia}} [[Ricky Ponting]]\n|92.85% (29 matches)\n|{{flagicon|West Indies}} [[Clive Lloyd]]\n|88.23% (17 matches)\n|<ref name=capt/>\n|}\n\n==See also==\n{{Portal|Cricket}}\n*[[List of One Day International cricket records]]\n*[[List of Cricket World Cup Centuries]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://cricket-records.com/pages/wc_records.htm List of Cricket World Cup Records from cricket-records.com]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20110829035927/http://www.cricketarchive.com/Archive/Records/Odis/WorldCup/index.html List of Cricket World Cup records from CricketArchive]\n* [http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/low/cricket/6327059.stm List of Cricket World Cup records from BBC]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20110123061323/http://www.worldcupofcricket.com/cricket-world-cup-records.php All Cricket World Cup records]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20150402113220/http://pcric.net/cricket-highlights/watch-martin-guptill-237-off-163-batting-video-highlights-vs-west-indies-21-3-2015-13586.html Martin 237 runs]\n\n{{Cricket World Cup}}\n{{Cricket records}}\n\n{{Featured list}}\n\n[[Category:One Day International cricket records|World Cup]]\n[[Category:Cricket World Cup|Records]]\n[[Category:Cricket-related lists|World Cup Records]]\n[[Category:Cricket World Cup-related lists|Records]]\n", "name_user": "202.142.184.203", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(\u2192\u200eHighest innings totals)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_Cricket_World_Cup_records"}
